Grootvlei, Orkney Gold Mines Attract Buyers, Business Day Says

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-05-27T05:23:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/aurora-s-grootvlei-orkney-gold-mines-attract-buyers-business-day-says.html
South Africa ’s Grootvlei and Orkney
gold mines, owned by a group linked to a nephew of President
 Jacob Zuma  and a grandson of  Nelson Mandela , has attracted the
interest of an unidentified JSE Ltd.-listed company, Business
Day reported.  A second unidentified company has also expressed an
interest in the mines, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said,
citing Gideon du Plessis, deputy secretary-general of the
Solidarity labor union.  China ’s Shandong Gold Mining Co. has also made an offer to
Aurora for the mines, Business Day said.  Grootvlei and Orkney were bought by Aurora Empowerment
Systems Ltd. after  Pamodzi Gold Ltd. (PZG)  went into liquidation.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  